<title>USA: Lugar warns on expansion of crop revenue insurance.</title>
<headline>Lugar warns on expansion of crop revenue insurance.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1997-01-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Senate Agriculture Commmittee Chairman Richard Lugar (R-Ind) warned the Secretary of Agriculture on Tuesday that expanding crop revenue insurance with large taxpayer subsidies would be a major concern to Congress and &quot;fiscally imprudent.&quot;</p>
<p>In a letter to Glickman, Lugar said he is &quot;concerned&quot; about the department's handling of the issue.</p>
<p>The USDA&quot;s Risk Management Agency is in the final weeks of negotiating with a private insurance company the terms of selling federally backed revenue insurance.</p>
</text>
